Melodi Grand Prix 2007 (shortened MGP 2007) was the television show in which the Norwegian entry for the Eurovision Song Contest 2007 was chosen.
Just like in 2006, there was be 3 semi finals held before the final, where televoting decided the Top 4 songs, the top 2 of who went to the final (in random order), and the songs who were placed 3rd and 4th go to the 'Second Chance' semi final (also in random order).
